quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And as We took from the Prophets their Compact and from you and from Nuh, and Ibrahim, and Musa, and Isa son of Maryam. (Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus of Mary respectively) And We took from them a solemn compact"
  33,8,That He might ask the sincere of their sincerity; and He has prepared for the disbelievers a painful torment
  33,9,"O you who have believed, remember the favor of Allah upon you as hosts came against you; then We sent against them a wind and hosts you did not see; and Allah has been Ever-Beholding whatever you do"
  33,10,"As they came against you from above you and from below you, and as beholdings swerved and hearts reached to the larynxes; and you surmised vain surmises about Allah"
  33,11,"Thereover were the believers tried, and were made to quake with a severe earthquake"
  33,12,"And as the hypocrites and the ones in whose hearts is sickness said, \"In no way did Allah and His Messenger promise us anything except delusion"
  33,13,"(And as a section of them said, \" O population of Yathrib, Al-Madinah) there is no stationing (here) for you, so return!\" And a group of them were asking permission of the Prophet, saying, \"Surely our houses are privacies.\" (Or: weak spots; i.e., They begged permission to protect their own homes) And in no way were they privacies; decidedly they would like (to seek) nothing except flight"
  33,14,"And if (the city) had been entered upon them from its (adjacent) regions, and thereafter they had been asked sedition, (Literally: temptation; i.e, if the hypocrites had been asked to apostatize from Islam) indeed they would have brought it forth and in no way would they have kept lingering in it except a little while. (Literally: an easy (while)"
  33,15,"And indeed they had already covenanted with Allah earlier, that they would not turn their backs; and a covenant with Allah will be questioned"